Related Technology

What is Monolithic Application ?

A monolithic application is self-contained, and independent from other computing applications

Typical Monolithic Application

Benefits

1. Easy to develop.
2. Easy to test.
3. Simple to deploy.
4. Relatively easier to scale.

Disadvantages

- Application too big.
- For every change entire application needs to be deployed.
- Bug in one system can bring down entire system.
- Very hard to introduce new technology.

Markup Language

Markup language is a system for annontating a document in a way that is syntactically distinguishable from other text.

In real world, paper text

Color Pens, Highlighter, Underline..

In Computer world, its Hyper Text

Hyper : Uplift / Lively / Refreshing Job of diffrentiating (from simple text) is done by <tags>

    Example of Tags

    <h1> Heading 1 </h1>
    <h2> Heading 2 </h2>
    <h3> Heading 3 </h3>
    <strong> Bold Text </strong>
    <i> Italicized Text </i>

Markdown Language

Lightweight language used with plain text to create Rich text output.

No fancy editors needed for creating Rich text.

Popularly used in Githubs (readme.md), Technical writers use this a lot

- It's Easy
- It's Fast
- It's Cross Platform
- It's Easy to read (without parsing)
- It's convertable

Note : This whole page was created using Markdown

    Example of Markdown

    # H1
    ## H2
    ### H3

    **Bold Text**

    *Italicized Text*

    >blockquote

Images

Image Types

JPG - Joint Photographic Expert Group

GIF - Graphic Interchange Format

PNG - Portaable Network Graphic

SVG - Scalable Vector Graphic

SVG Whats Special

- XML based, gaining popularity in recent years.
- Basically Text files that describes lines, curves, colors.
- Its human readable, can be modified easily manually as well as programatically.
- Its a W3C standard.
- Can be indexed and searched.
- Small in size.
- Enlarged without loss of quality

SVG Use Cases

(see demo)

- Diagrams
- Logos - Icons
- Animations
- Charts / Graphs / Maps

SVG How to create one

- Adobe Illustrator
- Inkscape
- Online converters for PNG to SVG
- Plotly (Python Library)
- Mermaid (see above)
